Package: leadsearch
Title: Gets Probable LinkedIn URLs and Job Descriptions
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Henrik", "Varmer", email = "henrik@varmer.dk", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Enriches a data frame of (name, email) pairs by querying the Google
    or Bing CustomSearch APIs (restricted to LinkedIn) to guess each person's
    job title, workplace and LinkedIn profile URL.
Depends: R (>= 3.4.3)
Imports:
    httr,
    stringr,
    stringi,
    textclean,
    utils
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
License: MIT + file LICENSE
URL: https://github.com/HenrikVarmer/LeadSearch
BugReports: https://github.com/HenrikVarmer/LeadSearch/issues
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Roxygen: list(markdown = FALSE)
RoxygenNote: 7.3.1
Config/testthat/edition: 3
